{{Infobox person | name = Justin Erenkrantz | image = Justin_Erenkrantz.jpg | image_size = | caption = Justin Erenkrantz at [[O'Reilly Open Source Convention|OSCON]] 2009 | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = | spouse = | parents = | children = }} '''Justin Erenkrantz''' was President of the [[Apache Software Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web | last = Mahon | first = Karen | title = Yahoo! Raises Commitment to Cloud Computing with the Availability of Yahoo! Distribution of Hadoop | publisher = Reuters | date = 06/10/09 | url = http://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS170727+10-Jun-2009+BW20090610 | accessdate = 09/10/09}}</ref><ref name = uci/> He previously served as Treasurer for the ASF. Erenkrantz works as a Senior [[Software Engineer]] for [[Joost]]. Erenkrantz has made major coding developments on [[Apache HTTP Server]], [[Apache Portable Runtime|APR]], mod_mbox, flood and Serf. As of 2010 Erenkrantz graduated from the [[University of California, Irvine]] where he received a PhD. His dissertation is titled ''Computational REST: A New Model for Decentralized, Internet-Scale Applications.''<ref name = uci>{{cite web | title = Department news 2007 | publisher = University of California, Irvine | date = 12/09 | url = http://www.ics.uci.edu/informatics/news/news_2007.php | accessdate = 09/10/09}}</ref><ref name=erenkrantz> {{cite web | title = erenkrantz | url = http://www.erenkrantz.com/ | accessdate = 01/12/10}}</ref><ref name="erenkrantz"/> <ref>{{cite web | title = Justin Erenkrantz | publisher = O'Reilly | date = 22 July 2009 | url = http://en.oreilly.com/oscon2009/public/schedule/speaker/27306 | accessdate = 09/10/09}}</ref>
